Does anyone have a tip for a mouse that is close to the Revoltec RE122 Fightmouse Elite? It's out of stock everywhere and my old one isn't going to hold up much longer I feel. I am specifically looking for a cable mouse that features adjustable weights and DPI, a place to put your small finger, because I always have my middlefinger on the wheel, and a larger size and braided cord. And I don't want a ton of little buttons on it. Two thumb buttons are ok, but I could even go without them, since I never use them. But it definetly needs a clicky wheel that also can be used to click.
And if someone knows a place where you can still get the fightmouse elite, that would be great.

snippet.textDisplay: Just save yourself the trouble and go with G305/G304. No cable. Light. Accurate and practically no latency (check Rocket Jump Ninja's review) and for a wireless mouse its service life is not tied to an unremovable battery. It nails all of the essentials for a gaming mouse, and has wireless freedom, and could potentially last forever. For a user focused on practicality, this is basically the holy grail of mice.
